article_text:
Last night’s State of the Union address “is best understood as the start of a campaign to persuade Americans that the last seven years have been better than they believe,” notes a Journal editorial. Mr. Obama “needs to start early because this reality makeover won’t be easy.”

Case in point, Mr. Obama asked Americans to view the disgraceful medical care provided to military veterans on his watch as an example of “the progress of these past seven years.” Mr. Obama also claimed victory on the economy, though Americans are...
